With holidays in full force, it’s hard to get away from all the sugary treats, extra helpings of food and of course, the liquid calories that often accompany them. 

So here’s an idea, don’t focus on weight gain, but rather weight-maintaining. 

If you know you’ll be indulging in a whole lot holiday cheer, make a commitment to yourself to add on some extra movement to keep that mental health in check. 

Many start the new year feeling guilty and shameful over a period of extra indulgence. We strive to live healthier lifestyles all year round but then take a holiday from the things that allow us to thrive… 

Here are some fun ways to burn a 100 calories  before you head into holiday party mode - remember you’ll be feeling great for doing the movements, so tendency to want to stay feeling great will assist with not overindulging. 

✅ Climb stairs for 10 minutes
✅ Do yoga for 30 minutes
✅ Walk for 30 minutes
✅ Do your work standing rather than sitting
✅ Jump rope for 7 minutes
✅ Dance for 30 minutes
✅ Do rigorous chores for 30 minutes
✅ Run a 10-minute mile
✅ Shovel snow for 10-minutes

And all else fails, 10 minutes of burpees will have you feeling awesome! (Maybe? 🤣)

Have a happy healthy holiday!

What’s your mobility routine entail?

For me, the ability to move well is directly correlated to my quality of life. 

If my ability to move is compromised, so too is my ability to enjoy my life. 

So, I commit a little time each day to ensure my body moves well and pain free. It takes time. It takes commitment. It takes a little discipline. But, I know what it is like to be on the other side too — years ago I suffered a nasty injury to my L4/L5 vertebrae. 

I was someone who loved to train, but I never stretched. I was always tight. Bending over to touch my toes was a workout in itself. But I thought I was healthy enough and everything was fine… until it wasn’t. 

It was awful. 

For 6 weeks I was practically bed ridden. Everything hurt. The most basic of movements like helping my kids in and out of bed hurt like a mofo. 

It took me 9 months of working my mobility, my core strength, and focused strength work to get back to functioning without pain. 

I’ll do my best to never get there again. And I know my mobility ritual of 5 to 20 minutes a day is to my body like flossing is to my teeth. A little each day keeps the doctors away! 

So, ready to get started on your own daily mobility practice? 

I have a 22 minute guided mobility routine I’d be happy to share with you. Just comment below or shoot me a DM and I’d be happy to share with you. 

Remember, movement is not to be taken for granted. Do something today that will make tomorrow easier. 💪🏻🙏

Change your emotional state in just 5 minutes... wondering how? ⁠
⁠
Read on...⁠
⁠
Understanding your happy hormones could help you to enhance your emotional well-being. Substances like dopamine and serotonin play a significant role in regulating your moods.⁠
⁠
What are hormones? ⁠
⁠
They’re messengers secreted by your glands and carried through your bloodstream. ⁠
⁠
Even in tiny amounts, they can cause major changes in your body. They also need to be kept in balance because they interact closely with each other.⁠
⁠
You can usually keep them functioning well by using gentle, natural methods or following your doctor’s recommendations if you develop a deficiency. ⁠
⁠
Learn more about your happy hormones and how to make them work for you.⁠
⁠
🚀 Dopamine⁠
⁠
Your brain’s pleasure and reward systems depend largely on dopamine. Dopamine is one of the reasons why you feel warm and fuzzy when you receive a compliment or any positive attention. It also helps with executive function and motor control.⁠
⁠
Use these strategies to boost your dopamine levels:⁠
⁠
✔ Fulfill your goals. ⁠
⁠
Adding to your accomplishments is a natural way to increase dopamine levels. Give yourself something to strive for each day and celebrate your victories.⁠
⁠
✔ Limit sugar. ⁠
⁠
Your diet matters too. Excess sugar and saturated fat can inhibit dopamine production. Cut back on empty calories and switch to healthier fats. Omega-3 fatty acids found in foods like fish and nuts actually boost dopamine.⁠
⁠
✔ Get some sun. ⁠
⁠
Vitamin D strengthens your bones and may increase dopamine. Spend time outdoors each day and check labels for foods fortified with vitamin D.⁠
⁠
✔ Listen to music. ⁠
⁠
One study found that dopamine levels increased by as much as 9% when volunteers listened to music that they enjoyed. Create playlists for exercising, working, and other daily activities.⁠
⁠
✔ Have fun. ⁠
⁠
While music may be especially influential, other healthy pleasures work too. Make time in your schedule for hanging out with family and friends and working on hobbies and other things you enjoy.

Hey, everyone! I've got a story about my recent gymnastics workshop experience, where I learned how to do muscle-ups. I hope it inspires you to step out of your comfort zone and embrace discomfort as a path to growth and success.

So, here it goes: I walked into the workshop at @crossfitbc feeling confident and excited, ready to tackle this new challenge. But as soon as I saw the gymnastic rings, my confidence turned into nervousness. "Can I really do this?" I thought to myself.

The coaches, @luluebertsgymnastics 
 and her husband, @ebertsmike, gave us a demonstration and made it look easy, but as I tried to pull myself up, my arms felt like noodles, and my grip started to slip. 

I couldn't even get halfway up! 

The false grip was not working for me....

I felt embarrassed and frustrated, but I didn't give up.

The coach noticed my struggle and offered helpful tips, strategies, and encouragement. I kept trying, and even though it was uncomfortable, I started to get more comfortable with feeling uncomfortable. I realized that progress takes time, and failing and trying again is okay.

Eventually, after many attempts and sweat, I completed my first muscle-up - I linked two in a row! 

It felt like a small victory but was a significant milestone in my personal growth journey. I learned that embracing discomfort is essential to achieve greatness and that pushing through discomfort is the only way to improve.

So, my friends, don't hesitate to leave your comfort zone, even if it means feeling uncomfortable. Embrace the discomfort, learn from your failures, and keep pushing forward. Who knows, you might surprise yourself with what you can achieve!

Let's take a moment to talk about something crucial yet often overlooked: the power of choosing the right emotions. 

Yes—emotions are a choice! 

In this fast-paced, high-pressure world, it's easy to get swept away by the currents of stress, frustration, or even anger. But let's pause for a second and remember that we can steer our emotional compass in a positive direction. 🧭

Why is this important? 

Well, think about it—our emotions influence our mindset, interactions, and ultimately our success. 

When we consciously choose to embrace the right emotions, we create a ripple effect that transforms not only our own lives but also the lives of those around us. 💫

So, how do we select the right emotional gear for professional success? 

1️⃣ Start with self-awareness

Take a moment to understand your emotional landscape. Acknowledge the emotions in different situations, and recognize how they impact your thoughts and actions. This self-awareness will help you identify the emotions that serve you best.

2️⃣ Choose empowerment over victimhood

It's natural to face challenges and setbacks, but how we react to them makes all the difference. Instead of dwelling on negativity, focus on finding solutions and opportunities for growth. Embrace resilience, determination, and a can-do attitude!

3️⃣ Practice empathy and understanding

The professional world is a melting pot of diverse personalities and perspectives. By cultivating empathy, you create an environment where collaboration and innovation thrive. Seek to understand others, appreciate their differences, and forge meaningful connections.

4️⃣ Foster a positive mindset 

Your mindset shapes your reality. Train your brain to focus on the positive aspects of every situation, even in the face of adversity. Embrace optimism, gratitude, and a solution-oriented approach. Your contagious positivity will inspire and uplift those around you. 🌞

Remember, choosing the right emotions isn't always easy; it takes practice and patience. But as professionals, we can mold our emotional landscape and create a harmonious and uplifting work environment.

⁠

⁠
Take a moment each day to reflect on what you're grateful for. In those 5 minutes, close your eyes, take a deep breath, and think about the blessings in your life, big and small. By acknowledging and appreciating these moments, you'll cultivate a sense of gratitude that can bring immense fulfillment.⁠
⁠
2️⃣ Mindful Breathing: ⁠
⁠
Find a quiet space and set aside 5 minutes for deep, intentional breathing. Close your eyes, inhale deeply through your nose, feeling the air filling your lungs, and then exhale slowly through your mouth. As you focus on your breath, let go of any tension or worries, allowing yourself to be fully present at the moment. These few minutes of mindful breathing can promote relaxation, reduce stress, and create greater fulfillment.⁠
⁠
3️⃣ Acts of Kindness: ⁠
⁠
Dedicate just 5 minutes each day to act kindly for someone else. It could be as simple as sending a thoughtful message to a loved one, complimenting a colleague, or helping a stranger in need. Extending kindness brightens someone else's day, and they experience a profound sense of fulfillment and connection. Small gestures can have a significant impact!⁠
⁠
Remember, fulfillment is a journey; small, intentional actions pave the way. ⁠
⁠
With just 5 minutes of focused attention daily, you can invite more gratitude, mindfulness, and kindness into your life. Start today and embrace the transformative impact of these tiny moments! 🌟💫⁠

#FitTipFriday: Here is a simple way to start your day on a positive note… everytime! 

Feeling positive and energized from the moment you wake up can set the tone for an amazing day ahead. 

Here are some simple yet effective tips to help you start your day on a positive note:

1️⃣ Rise and Shine with Gratitude: 

As soon as you wake up, take a moment to reflect on the things you are grateful for. Whether it's the cozy bed you slept in or the people you love, expressing gratitude can uplift your spirits and foster a positive mindset.

Begin your day with gentle stretches or a short yoga session. It not only promotes physical well-being but also boosts mental clarity and increases your body's energy levels. Focus on deep, intentional breaths to calm your mind and invigorate your body.

Start your morning with a nutritious breakfast to provide your body with essential nutrients and fuel for the day. A balanced meal that includes whole grains, protein, healthy fats, and fruits or vegetables will help keep your energy levels stable and uplift your mood.

4️⃣ Set Positive Intentions: 

Take a few moments to set your intentions for the day. Visualize what you would like to achieve or how you want to feel throughout the day. Emphasize positive affirmations and remind yourself of your strengths and capabilities.

5️⃣ Enjoy Moments of Stillness: 

Find time for meditation or reflection to cultivate a sense of calm and inner peace. Even a few minutes of quiet mindfulness can help reduce stress, improve focus, and bring a positive outlook to your day.

6️⃣ Connect with Loved Ones: 

Reach out to someone you care about, share a kind message, or spend quality time with a loved one. Connection and positive social interactions are important for maintaining overall well-being and can contribute to a happier start to your day.

Remember, starting your day with a positive mindset can have a profound impact on your well-being and productivity.

Kettlebell windmills are an excellent exercise movement because they offer a unique combination of strength training, flexibility, and functional fitness. 

They engage multiple muscle groups, including the obliques, hamstrings, shoulders, and back, while enhancing shoulder stability and thoracic spine mobility. 

The movement mimics real-life bending and reaching motions, making it a functional exercise that can aid in daily activities. 

Moreover, the windmill promotes core strength and stability, which are fundamental for overall physical health and injury prevention. This multi-faceted exercise can be a valuable addition to any fitness regimen.

Here's how to perform a windmill...

Starting Position:

✅ Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.
✅ Hold a kettlebell (or dumbbell) in your right hand.
✅ Press the kettlebell overhead, locking out your arm and ensuring your wrist is straight.
✅ Rotate your feet at a 45-degree angle to the left.

Movement:

✅ Keep your eyes on the kettlebell throughout the movement.
✅ Push your hips to the right while keeping the kettlebell arm straight and overhead.
✅ Start bending to the left at the waist, keeping your legs straight.
✅ Slide your left hand down your left leg as far as your flexibility allows. Ideally, you'll touch the ground, but it's okay if you can't initially.
✅ Your body should form a triangle with the floor during the deepest part of the movement.

Return:

✅ Engage your obliques, straighten up,
 and return to the starting position.

Switch Sides:

✅ After completing the desired number of reps on one side, switch the kettlebell to the other hand and repeat on the opposite side.

Tips:

✅ Keep the kettlebell arm straight and your wrist neutral.
✅ The kettlebell should be positioned directly above your shoulder throughout the exercise.
✅ Your back should be straight and hinge at the hips.
✅ Always maintain a slow, controlled motion.

It's essential to warm up before performing this exercise and to start with a lightweight until you master the form.

If you're new to windmill exercise or have any medical conditions, it's a good idea to consult a fitness professional or physical therapist before attempting it.

I remember those early mornings as a child, groggily shuffling into the living room to find the day already in full swing. 

The sun would be peeking through the curtains, casting warm beams of light onto the carpet. And there, right in the middle of that sunlight, was Mom, moving energetically in rhythm to the upbeat tunes on our old television.

It wasn't just any workout routine; it was Richard Simmons’ “Sweatin' to the Oldies” on VHS. The sight was nothing short of magical for my young eyes. Mom, with her leg warmers and big hair – a total '80s queen – was dancing, laughing, and, yes, sweating it out to the contagious energy of Richard Simmons.

Sometimes, she noticed me watching her and would reach out her hand, inviting me to join her. I'd laugh and mimic her steps, failing most times hilariously -- all very reminiscent of my days today with my own daughters trying to teach me the newest TikTok moves... I still DON'T get it! 

But what stayed with me wasn't the fancy footwork or the catchy oldies. It was the sparkle in her eyes, the infectious laughter, and the sheer joy of those moments.

Those mornings taught me early on about the power of self-care, persistence, and finding joy in the simple things. While the world outside was often chaotic and challenging, our living room became a sanctuary of positivity and fun. The message was clear - it wasn't about perfection or looking a certain way. It was about moving, laughing, and celebrating life.

Years later, I remember those mornings when I face challenges or need a pick-me-up. 

I think of Mom, dancing without a care in the world, powered by Richard Simmons' positive vibes. And I'm reminded that sometimes, all you need to do is dance through the tough times, and everything will be alright.

That old VHS tape, with its worn-out edges, might be collecting dust somewhere in a dark recess of a thrift store. But its spirit, the lessons it imparted, and the memories it created are alive in me. And for that, I'll forever be grateful.

The Med Ball Thoracic Plate Extension is a dynamic exercise targeting the thoracic region of the spine. (What I’m doing in this video is a modified version) 

This movement involves lying face up, typically on a bench, with a medicine ball held overhead. The exerciser extends their arms and upper back over the ball, enhancing the stretch and mobility in the thoracic spine. 

This exercise is awesome for several reasons:

1. **Improves Thoracic Mobility**: It specifically targets the thoracic spine, which is crucial for overall spine health and flexibility. This area often becomes stiff due to poor posture and sedentary lifestyles.
 
2. **Enhances Posture**: Regular practice can help correct rounded shoulders and forward head posture, common issues in today’s desk-bound society.
 
3. **Supports Upper Body Exercises**: Better thoracic mobility can improve performance in upper body exercises like overhead presses and squats by allowing for a fuller range of motion.
 
4. **Reduces Back Pain**: By increasing flexibility and strength in the upper back, it can help alleviate general back discomfort.
 
5. **Accessible and Scalable**: It’s a simple yet effective exercise that can be performed with minimal equipment and easily adjusted for different fitness levels.

6️⃣. Embrace Failures: They’re stepping stones, not roadblocks. Each failure brings you closer to success.

7️⃣. Visualize Success: Picture yourself succeeding. Visualization can significantly improve your ability to handle challenges.

8️⃣ Laugh It Off: Find humor in your “I can’ts.” Laughter reduces stress and helps you see things differently.

Remember, switching from “I can’t” to “I can” is about seeing possibilities where you once saw barriers. 

So, laugh a little, start small, and who knows?

And with high sugar intake linked to all sorts of party poopers like increased risk of heart disease, weight gain, and even affect our mood, it's a relationship we ought to reconsider.⁠
